Package application.client.managers

Class ViewManager

java.lang.Object
application.client.managers.ViewManager
public class ViewManager extends Object
This class is a singleton pattern. This class is used to manage the display of views.
Author:
Federico Canali

    • getInstance

      public static ViewManager getInstance()
      The constructor is called only if the static instance is null, so only the first time that the getInstance() method is invoked. All the other times the same instance object is returned.
      Returns:
      the instance object is returned.

      public void showLayout(String page)

    • showLayout

      public void showLayout(float price, Object objectToInsert, String operation)
      Show the payment layout.
      Parameters:
      price - It represents the price to pay for this operation.
      objectToInsert - Represents a possible object to manage once passed. It depends on the type of payment.
      operation - Represents the type of payment that will have to be made.
